			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2020</a> paper:</span><br><i>An Interactive Feedback System for Grammar Development (tool paper)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ChelseaBarraball.html">Chelsea Barraball</a>, <a href="../profile/MoeketsiRaselimo.html">Moeketsi Raselimo</a>, <a href="../profile/BerndFischer.html">Bernd Fischer</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3426425.3426935">10.1145/3426425.3426935</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> The paper primarily contributes techniques for language definition (often syntax-related) as part of language design.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It performs mapping/conversion/synchronization between representations (horizontal transformations).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> It targets usability (developer interaction, comprehension, editing experience).
</li></ul></li></ul>
